  "prompt": "How do I reset my Gmail password when I don't remember my recovery information? Request",
  "response": "Here are steps to reset your Gmail password when you don't remember recovery information:\n\n1. Go to the Google Account recovery page\n\u2022 Visit accounts.google.com/signin/recovery\n\n2. Enter your email address\n\n3. Click \"Forgot password?\"\n\n4. If you can't verify through standard methods:\n\u2022 Select \"Try another way\"\n\u2022 Choose available verification options\n\nAlternative methods:\n\u2022 Use a phone number previously linked\n\u2022 Verify through a backup email\n\u2022 Answer security questions\n\u2022 Use a previously authorized device\n\nIf no recovery options work:\n\u2022 Visit Google's account recovery support page\n\u2022 Fill out the account recovery form\n\u2022 Provide proof of account ownership\n\u2022 May need to verify identity with government ID\n\nAdditional tips:\n\u2022 Have patience with the process\n\u2022 Provide as much accurate information as possible\n\u2022 Check spam/alternative email folders for recovery instructions\n\u2022 Consider creating new recovery information for future access\n\nWarning:\n\u2022 Account recovery can take several days\n\u2022 Some information might be permanently unrecoverable\n\u2022 Google has strict verification processes\n\nPreventative steps:\n\u2022 Always keep recovery information updated\n\u2022 Use multiple recovery methods\n\u2022 Consider using a password manager\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
